Abdel-Kader Russell-Boumzar was granted bail in Brisbane Magistrate Court on Thursday . 
  The 17-year-old was jailed in January for a string of alleged offences . 
  He allegedly racially abused a train guard on a Brisbane train last October . 
  Footage of him allegedly spitting on the guard went viral . 
  He was charged with serious assault, creating a disturbance and racial vilification . 
  Magistrate Deborah Vasta warned him he was 'public enemy number one' He was released on bail after a 69 day stint behind bars . 
 